data.title: European Royal Families
data.meta_description: bécsi fillérek - Free ebook download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read book online for free. This document provides background information on silver coins and coinage in Austria during the Middle Ages. It discusses the various ruling margraves and dukes of Austria from 976 to 1177, including Leopold I, the first margrave of the Babenberg dynasty, and Henry II who elevated Austria to a duchy in 1156 and moved his residence to Vienna, establishing it as the capital. The document also notes some territorial expansions and founding of monasteries during the rules of various margraves.
